Thermite bombs are expensive, unsafe to data and others, inelegant,
unreliable, difficult to use, and will void the warranties of all
major PC brands except Gateway.  

Even if expertly implemented, it would not provide the kind of
protection Peter and I were talking about.

We're discussing cryptology here.  Take it to rec.pyrotechnic.

(Sorry if I seem rude.  Thermite flames are supposed to be hot.)

